data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both work exactly as you'd expect:

```csharp
Span<nint> nints = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> nuints = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

On this 64-bit runtime, each element is 8 bytes. The only quirk is that `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context (since the size isn't known at compile time), but you can use `nint.Size` instead.
